definitions.definition: An island of the Dodecanese , Greece in the Aegean Sea .
A city on the island of Rhodes , Greece , and the capital of the Dodecanese.

main_definition: An island of the Dodecanese , Greece in the Aegean Sea .
secondary_definitions: A city on the island of Rhodes , Greece , and the capital of the Dodecanese.

definitions.definition: A topographic surname for a person who lived near woodland clearings, or a habitational one for someone from a place so named.
A male given name transferred from the surname .
A village in northern Eastern Cape province, South Africa ; named for Cecil Rhodes.
A number of places in the United States :

subdefinitions.definition: An unincorporated community in Clinton Township, Vermillion County , Indiana .
A minor city in Marshall County , Iowa ; named for Conway B. Rhodes.
An unincorporated community in Bentley Township, Gladwin County , Michigan ; named for Murry Bentley Rhodes.
A census-designated place in Flathead County , Montana .

definitions.definition: A village near Middleton , Rochdale borough , Greater Manchester , England ( OS grid ref SD8505 ) .
A small commune in Moselle department, Lorraine , Grand Est , France .
A suburb of Sydney , in the City of Canada Bay , New South Wales , Australia .
An electric piano which produces soft, harmonic -like sounds; a Rhodes piano ; named for inventor Harold Rhodes.
